The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Four persons were injured when a car in the convoy of the Union minister of state for heavy industry, Raghunath Jha, fell in a ditch beside National Highway 6 near Domjur, in Howrah, on Sunday afternoon. The convoy was on its way to Uluberia. The four injured were travelling in the car. The mishap occurred when one of the rear wheels of the car became loose and the driver lost control, said a police officer.    Sovarani Das, 55, was run over by a car while she was crossing the road in Mathkal, Belghoria, on Sunday afternoon. Residents blocked the road till 2.30pm and prevented police from taking away Sovaranis body. The blockade was lifted after a large police contingent went to the spot and senior officers assured the protesters of taking measures against rash driving.    A youth died after being hit by a tram near the Hazra crossing on SP Mukherjee Road on Saturday night. Babloo Das, 25, was taken to SSKM Hospital, where he was declared dead.    Ramen Halder, 50, was electrocuted in Begri Sitalatala, under Domjur police station, on Saturday night. Police said Halder was on his way to his shop at Begribazar around 11.30pm when he stepped on a live electric wire. He died on the spot. The body has been sent for post-mortem.    A motorcycle each was stolen from South Sinthee Road, under Sinthee police station, and Dr Subhash Lane, under Chitpur police station, in the past 24 hours. The thieves broke the locks of the two motorcycles that were parked in the open. No one has been arrested.    The civic parks and gardens wing of the Calcutta Municipal Corporation has taken up a scheme to plant 80,000 fruit saplings in parks and on the banks of drainage canals. Mayoral council member (parks and gardens) Faiyaz Ahmed Khan said the drive would also cover parks that are not owned by the civic body. Saplings of mango, litchi and guava will be planted.    Four members of a family were injured after being struck by lightning on Sunday afternoon in Barasat, on the northern fringes of the city. Rabiul Islam was watching TV with his wife and two children around 2.30pm when his tin-roofed house caught fire after being struck by lightning. The four were taken to Barasat district hospital where their condition was stated to be critical.     A former employee of the Calcutta Municipal Corporation committed suicide by hanging himself in his house in Salbagan, Barasat, on Sunday. Police said a paralytic Robin Ghosh, 47, was bedridden for the past two months and was suffering from depression. He was taken to hospital where he was declared dead on arrival. Ghosh killed himself when his wife and son were out.            
